{"ts":"2026-06-26T21:16:10.826Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Examining Swift Progress**\n\nI'm incredibly pleased with the elegant and swift progress. Now, my focus shifts to integrating the form wizard stepper. I plan to replace the placeholder with the complete form code for Steps 1, 2, and 3. I've paused momentarily to assess the form code's size, which includes the draft notice.\n\n\n**Assessing Code Implementation**\n\nThe form code, including the draft notice and navigation, is roughly 5500 characters. Happily, that keeps me well below the 6000 character limit! I'm now drafting the code for integration, specifically focusing on the step selector, active step baselines, path selection, budget, stakeholders, and buttons.\n\n\n**Analyzing Step Interface**\n\nI'm currently focused on the step timeline gate header implementation. I've been dissecting the code that handles step navigation and validation logic, specifically for the Baseline Profile, Strategy & Challenges, and Deployment Pathway steps. My primary aim is to understand the conditional rendering of these steps and its relation to the `activeStepGate` state. I'm also examining the `validateStep()` function and how it impacts the navigation flow.\n\n\n**Dissecting UI Implementation**\n\nI'm currently focused on the UI implementation for the baseline gate. I've been dissecting the code to understand how the conditional rendering works within the `activeStepGate` state. My goal is to grasp how the \"Corporate Baseline Profile\" section and its input fields are displayed and managed in the current step. I'm especially interested in how the styling is applied with the different classes.\n\n\n**Refining Field Integration**\n\nI'm now integrating the `onChange` event handler for the company name input field. I'm focusing on how `setInputs` updates the state with the user's input. Simultaneously, I'm examining the `placeholder` text, class names for styling, and how the focus and border behave. Next, I'll integrate the input for industry vertical selection, evaluating the validation logic and error display.\n\n\n**Integrating Industry Selection**\n\nI'm now integrating the industry vertical selection. I'm focused on the button's `onClick` handler, specifically how `setInputs` updates the `inputs` state with the selected industry's ID, and how validation errors are cleared using `setValidationErrors`. I am also looking at the conditional class names, which are styling the selected button. Finally, I'm examining the `label`, `desc`, and `icon` display.\n\n\n**Evaluating Input Field Logic**\n\nI'm now implementing the company size input field. I'm focused on the button's `onClick` handler. Specifically, I'm analyzing how `setInputs` updates the `inputs` state with the selected company size, while simultaneously clearing the `companySize` validation error using `setValidationErrors`. I'm paying close attention to the conditional class names, which are responsible for styling the selected button, and the related error display. I'm also ensuring the field validates.\n\n\n**Implementing Geography Input**\n\nI'm now integrating the deployment geography input. I'm focusing on the `onChange` handler, specifically how `setInputs` updates the `inputs` state with the geography value. I'm also examining the placeholder text, class names for styling, and how the input field handles focus and border. Next, I'll review any validation logic and error display, as needed.\n\n\n**Implementing Strategy Integration**\n\nI'm now integrating the primary obstacle input, focusing on the `onChange` event handler, examining how `setInputs` updates state. I'm also ensuring the `validationErrors` are correctly displayed and the field styling meets the design, and testing the error display logic.\n\n\n**Implementing Challenge Logic**\n\nI'm now integrating the primary challenge input and analyzing the code block. I'm focusing on the `onClick` event handler and how `setInputs` updates the `inputs` state with the selected challenge ID, while also clearing validation errors. I'm paying attention to the conditional class names, which are responsible for styling the selected button, and the related error display and ensuring the error messages are updated.\n\n\n**Implementing Custom Challenge**\n\nI'm now integrating the custom challenge input field, specifically the text area. I'm focusing on the conditional rendering tied to the \"other\" challenge selection. I'm making sure `onChange` updates the `inputs` state with the value of `customChallenge` and clears any associated validation errors, as well as the error message's display. I'm also ensuring the styling and placeholder text look right.\n\n\n**Refining Outcome Integration**\n\nI'm now integrating the priority outcomes input, and I am focused on the `onClick` event handler and how it manages the state updates. Specifically, I'm examining how `setInputs` updates the `inputs` state to include or exclude the selected outcome IDs, as well as the error handling. I'm also paying close attention to the visual styling changes based on selection and validation, ensuring correct error display.\n\n\n**Examining UI Updates**\n\nI'm now integrating the priority outcomes input, focused on how the `onClick` event handles state updates, specifically, how `setInputs` modifies the `inputs` state, including or excluding selected outcome IDs, as well as the error handling. I'm also examining the styling changes that depend on selection and validation, making sure errors display correctly.\n\n\n**Integrating Timeline Elements**\n\nI'm now integrating the target project timeline input, specifically focusing on the button's `onClick` handler and how `setInputs` updates the `inputs` state with the selected timeline ID and the validation errors are cleared. I'm also focused on the `isSelected` state, the conditional class names, and error display logic. Finally, I'm examining how the styling will be applied.\n\n\n**Integrating Deployment Logic**\n\nI'm now integrating the deployment pathway input, analyzing the button's `onClick` handler. I'm focusing on how `setInputs` updates the `inputs` state with the selected pathway ID, while clearing the validation errors. I'm also examining the `isSelected` state, conditional styling classes, and the error display logic to ensure seamless integration and validation.\n\n\n**Evaluating Engagement Pathway**\n\nI'm now integrating the sovereign engagement pathway section and scrutinizing the code. I'm focused on the button's `onClick` handler, precisely how `setInputs` updates the `inputs` state with the `preferredEngagementPath` ID. I'm ensuring the validation errors are cleared appropriately, and also analyzing the conditional class names, the state handling, and error display for a solid integration.\n\n\n**Integrating Engagement Options**\n\nI'm now integrating the sovereign engagement pathway input. I've focused on the `onClick` event, ensuring `setInputs` correctly updates the state with the `preferredEngagementPath` ID and that validation errors are cleared. The conditional styling and error display logic are under review. I'm also examining the conditional class names, the state handling, and error display for a solid integration.\n\n\n**Integrating Budget Values**\n\nI'm now integrating the budget values. The process involves scrutinizing the code that handles the budget range selection, focusing on how `setInputs` updates the state with the selected `budgetRange` ID. I'm carefully reviewing the error display to ensure smooth integration and validation. I'm also examining how the styling will be applied.\n\n\n**Refining Stakeholder Input**\n\nI'm now implementing the stakeholder input field and am dissecting its associated logic. I'm focused on the `onChange` handler, and ensuring `setInputs` properly updates the stakeholders state with the input. I'm also confirming that the styling of this input meets design requirements.\n\n\n**Analyzing Input Implementation**\n\nI'm now integrating the stakeholder input, ensuring the `onChange` event properly updates the stakeholders' state. I am focusing on input validation and handling, along with the styling and visual feedback for error conditions.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T21:16:10.831Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"vuqebo2n","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/build/proposal/page.tsx","old_text":"              {/* PLACEHOLDER_FORM_CARD */}","new_text":"              {hasSavedDraft && (\n                <div className=\"p-4 rounded-xl border border-[#009DFF]/20 bg-[#009DFF]/5 flex items-center justify-between text-xs text-white\">\n                  <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2\">\n                    <span className=\"w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[#009DFF] animate-pulse\" />\n                    <span>In-progress draft detected from your previous workspace session.</span>\n                  </div>\n                  <div className=\"flex gap-2\">\n                    <button onClick={handleRestoreDraft} className=\"px-3 py-1.5 bg-[#009DFF]/20 border border-[#009DFF]/40 text-[#009DFF] text-[10px] font-mono hover:bg-[#009DFF]/40 transition uppercase font-bold rounded\">Restore Draft</button>\n                    <button onClick={() => setHasSavedDraft(false)} className=\"px-2 py-1.5 text-white/40 text-[10px] font-mono hover:text-white uppercase\">Ignore</button>\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n              )}\n\n              {/* STEP TIMELINE GATE HEADER */}\n              <div className=\"p-1 rounded-lg bg-black/45 border border-white/5 flex text-center text-[10px] font-mono\">\n                {[1, 2, 3].map((g) => (\n                  <button\n                    key={g}\n                    type=\"button\"\n                    onClick={() => { if (validateStep(1) && (g < 3 || validateStep(2))) setActiveStepGate(g as 1 | 2 | 3); }}\n                    className={`flex-1 py-2 rounded transition font-semibold uppercase ${activeStepGate === g ? \"bg-white/5 text-[#009DFF] border border-white/10\" : \"text-white/40 hover:text-white\"}`}\n                    disabled={g > activeStepGate && !validateStep(activeStepGate)}\n                  >\n                    0{g} // {g === 1 ? \"Baseline Profile\" : g === 2 ? \"Strategy & Challenges\" : \"Deployment Pathway\"}\n                  </button>\n                ))}\n              </div>\n\n              {/* FORM WRAPPER CARD */}\n              <div className=\"p-6 lg:p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/5 bg-[#030306]/95 relative overflow-hidden\">\n                <div className=\"absolute top-0 right-0 p-4 font-mono text-[8px] text-white/20\">\n                  GFF_PROPOSAL_STUDIO // REV_2026\n                </div>\n\n                {/* GATE 1: BASELINE */}\n                {activeStepGate === 1 && (\n                  <div className=\"space-y-5\">\n                    <div className=\"border-b border-white/5 pb-3\">\n                      <span className=\"text-[9px] font-mono text-[#009DFF] uppercase tracking-wider font-bold\">GATE 01 OF 03</span>\n                      <h2 className=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mt-1\">Corporate Baseline Profile</h2>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div className=\"space-y-1.5\">\n                      <label className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50 uppercase tracking-wide block\">Organization Name (Optional)</label>\n                      <input\n                        type=\"text\"\n                        value={inputs.companyName}\n                        onChange={(e) => setInputs({ ...inputs, companyName: e.target.value })}\n                        placeholder=\"e.g. Sovereign Global Mainframes\"\n                        className=\"w-full bg-black/40 border border-white/10 rounded-lg px-4 h-11 text-xs text-white placeholder-white/20 focus:outline-none focus:border-[#009DFF]/60 transition\"\n                      />\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div className=\"space-y-1.5\">\n                      <div className=\"flex justify-between\">\n                        <label className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50 uppercase tracking-wide\">Industry Vertical</label>\n                        {validationErrors.industry && <span className=\"text-[9px] font-mono text-[#E4000F] font-bold\">{validationErrors.industry}</span>}\n                      </div>\n                      <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-2.5\">\n                        {INDUSTRIES.map((ind) => (\n                          <button\n                            key={ind.id}\n                            type=\"button\"\n                            onClick={() => { setInputs({ ...inputs, industry: ind.id }); setValidationErrors((prev) => ({ ...prev, industry: \"\" })); }}\n                            className={`p-3 rounded-xl border text-left transition flex gap-3 items-start min-h-[60px] ${inputs.industry === ind.id ? \"border-[#009DFF] bg-[#009DFF]/5\" : \"border-white/5 bg-black/40 hover:border-white/10\"}`}\n                          >\n                            <span className=\"text-base mt-0.5\">{ind.icon}</span>\n                            <div>\n                              <h4 className=\"text-xs font-bold text-white leading-none\">{ind.label}</h4>\n                              <p className=\"text-[9px] text-white/40 leading-snug font-light mt-1\">{ind.desc}</p>\n                            </div>\n                          </button>\n                        ))}\n                      </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div className=\"space-y-1.5\">\n                      <div className=\"flex justify-between\">\n                        <label className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50 uppercase tracking-wide\">Enterprise Scale</label>\n                        {validationErrors.companySize && <span className=\"text-[9px] font-mono text-[#E4000F] font-bold\">{validationErrors.companySize}</span>}\n                      </div>\n                      <div className=\"grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-2.5\">\n                        {COMPANY_SIZES.map((size) => (\n                          <button\n                            key={size.id}\n                            type=\"button\"\n                            onClick={() => { setInputs({ ...inputs, companySize: size.id }); setValidationErrors((prev) => ({ ...prev, companySize: \"\" })); }}\n                            className={`p-3 rounded-xl border text-left transition flex flex-col justify-between min-h-[95px] ${inputs.companySize === size.id ? \"border-[#009DFF] bg-[#009DFF]/5\" : \"border-white/5 bg-black/40 hover:border-white/10\"}`}\n                          >\n                            <div>\n                              <h4 className=\"text-xs font-bold text-white leading-tight\">{size.label}</h4>\n                              <span className=\"text-[8px] font-mono text-white/40 mt-0.5 block\">{size.range}</span>\n                            </div>\n                            <p className=\"text-[9px] text-white/30 leading-tight mt-1.5\">{size.desc}</p>\n                          </button>\n                        ))}\n                      </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div className=\"space-y-1.5\">\n                      <label className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50 uppercase tracking-wide block\">Deployment Geography (Optional)</label>\n                      <input\n                        type=\"text\"\n                        value={inputs.geography}\n                        onChange={(e) => setInputs({ ...inputs, geography: e.target.value })}\n                        placeholder=\"e.g. EU Sovereign Boundary (VPC Frankfurt)\"\n                        className=\"w-full bg-black/40 border border-white/10 rounded-lg px-4 h-11 text-xs text-white placeholder-white/20 focus:outline-none focus:border-[#009DFF]/60 transition\"\n                      />\n                    </div>\n                  </div>\n                )}\n\n                {/* GATE 2: STRATEGY & OUTCOMES */}\n                {activeStepGate === 2 && (\n                  <div className=\"space-y-5\">\n                    <div className=\"border-b border-white/5 pb-3\">\n                      <span className=\"text-[9px] font-mono text-[#009DFF] uppercase tracking-wider font-bold\">GATE 02 OF 03</span>\n                      <h2 className=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mt-1\">Strategic Friction & Outcomes</h2>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div className=\"space-y-1.5\">\n                      <div className=\"flex justify-between\">\n                        <label className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50 uppercase tracking-wide\">Primary Obstacle</label>\n                        {validationErrors.primaryChallenge && <span className=\"text-[9px] font-mono text-[#E4000F] font-bold\">{validationErrors.primaryChallenge}</span>}\n                      </div>\n                      <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-2.5\">\n                        {CHALLENGES.map((chal) => (\n                          <button\n                            key={chal.id}\n                            type=\"button\"\n                            onClick={() => { setInputs({ ...inputs, primaryChallenge: chal.id }); setValidationErrors((prev) => ({ ...prev, primaryChallenge: \"\" })); }}\n                            className={`p-3 rounded-xl border text-left transition flex gap-3 items-start min-h-[75px] ${inputs.primaryChallenge === chal.id ? \"border-[#009DFF] bg-[#009DFF]/5\" : \"border-white/5 bg-black/40 hover:border-white/10\"}`}\n                          >\n                            <span className=\"text-base mt-0.5\">{chal.icon}</span>\n                            <div>\n                              <h4 className=\"text-xs font-bold text-white leading-none\">{chal.label}</h4>\n                              <p className=\"text-[9px] text-white/35 leading-relaxed mt-1 font-light\">{chal.desc}</p>\n                            </div>\n                          </button>\n                        ))}\n                      </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    {inputs.primaryChallenge === \"other\" && (\n                      <motion.div initial={{ opacity: 0, height: 0 }} animate={{ opacity: 1, height: \"auto\" }} className=\"space-y-1.5\">\n                        <label className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50 uppercase tracking-wide block\">Specify Custom Obstacle</label>\n                        <textarea\n                          rows={2}\n                          value={inputs.customChallenge}\n                          onChange={(e) => { setInputs({ ...inputs, customChallenge: e.target.value }); setValidationErrors((prev) => ({ ...prev, customChallenge: \"\" })); }}\n                          placeholder=\"Describe the barrier we must architect against...\"\n                          className=\"w-full bg-black/40 border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-3 text-xs text-white focus:outline-none focus:border-[#009DFF]\"\n                        />\n                        {validationErrors.customChallenge && <span className=\"text-[9px] font-mono text-[#E4000F] font-bold\">{validationErrors.customChallenge}</span>}\n                      </motion.div>\n                    )}\n\n                    <div className=\"space-y-1.5\">\n                      <div className=\"flex justify-between\">\n                        <label className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50 uppercase tracking-wide\">Priority Outcomes</label>\n                        {validationErrors.priorityOutcomes && <span className=\"text-[9px] font-mono text-[#E4000F] font-bold\">{validationErrors.priorityOutcomes}</span>}\n                      </div>\n                      <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-2.5\">\n                        {OUTCOMES.map((out) => {\n                          const isSelected = inputs.priorityOutcomes.includes(out.id);\n                          return (\n                            <button\n                              key={out.id}\n                              type=\"button\"\n                              onClick={() => {\n                                let list = [...inputs.priorityOutcomes];\n                                if (isSelected) list = list.filter((id) => id !== out.id);\n                                else list.push(out.id);\n                                setInputs({ ...inputs, priorityOutcomes: list });\n                                setValidationErrors((prev) => ({ ...prev, priorityOutcomes: \"\" }));\n                              }}\n                              className={`p-3 rounded-xl border text-left transition flex items-center justify-between gap-4 ${isSelected ? \"border-[#009DFF] bg-[#009DFF]/5\" : \"border-white/5 bg-black/40 hover:border-white/10\"}`}\n                            >\n                              <div>\n                                <h4 className=\"text-xs font-bold text-white leading-tight\">{out.label}</h4>\n                                <p className=\"text-[9px] text-white/35 font-light leading-tight mt-1\">{out.desc}</p>\n                              </div>\n                              <div className={`w-3.5 h-3.5 rounded border flex items-center justify-center transition-all ${isSelected ? \"bg-[#009DFF] border-[#009DFF]\" : \"border-white/20 bg-black/50\"}`}>\n                                {isSelected && <span className=\"w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-black\" />}\n                              </div>\n                            </button>\n                          );\n                        })}\n                      </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div className=\"space-y-1.5\">\n                      <div className=\"flex justify-between\">\n                        <label className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50 uppercase tracking-wide\">Target Project Timeline</label>\n                        {validationErrors.targetTimeline && <span className=\"text-[9px] font-mono text-[#E4000F] font-bold\">{validationErrors.targetTimeline}</span>}\n                      </div>\n                      <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-2.5\">\n                        {TIMELINES.map((t) => (\n                          <button\n                            key={t.id}\n                            type=\"button\"\n                            onClick={() => { setInputs({ ...inputs, targetTimeline: t.id }); setValidationErrors((prev) => ({ ...prev, targetTimeline: \"\" })); }}\n                            className={`p-2.5 rounded-xl border text-left transition flex flex-col justify-between min-h-[85px] ${inputs.targetTimeline === t.id ? \"border-[#009DFF] bg-[#009DFF]/5\" : \"border-white/5 bg-black/40 hover:border-white/10\"}`}\n                          >\n                            <h4 className=\"text-[11px] font-bold text-white leading-tight\">{t.label}</h4>\n                            <p className=\"text-[8.5px] text-white/35 leading-snug mt-1 font-light\">{t.desc}</p>\n                          </button>\n                        ))}\n                      </div>\n                    </div>\n                  </div>\n                )}\n\n                {/* GATE 3: PATHWAY */}\n                {activeStepGate === 3 && (\n                  <div className=\"space-y-5\">\n                    <div className=\"border-b border-white/5 pb-3\">\n                      <span className=\"text-[9px] font-mono text-[#009DFF] uppercase tracking-wider font-bold\">GATE 03 OF 03</span>\n                      <h2 className=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mt-1\">Sovereign Engagement Pathway</h2>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div className=\"space-y-2\">\n                      <div className=\"flex justify-between\">\n                        <label className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50 uppercase tracking-wide\">Strategic Integration Path</label>\n                        {validationErrors.preferredEngagementPath && <span className=\"text-[9px] font-mono text-[#E4000F] font-bold\">{validationErrors.preferredEngagementPath}</span>}\n                      </div>\n                      <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3\">\n                        {ENGAGEMENT_PATHS.map((path) => {\n                          const isSelected = inputs.preferredEngagementPath === path.id;\n                          return (\n                            <button\n                              key={path.id}\n                              type=\"button\"\n                              onClick={() => { setInputs({ ...inputs, preferredEngagementPath: path.id }); setValidationErrors((prev) => ({ ...prev, preferredEngagementPath: \"\" })); }}\n                              className={`p-3.5 rounded-xl border text-left transition flex flex-col justify-between min-h-[160px] relative overflow-hidden ${isSelected ? \"border-[#009DFF] bg-[#030307]\" : \"border-white/5 bg-black/40 hover:border-white/10\"}`}\n                            >\n                              <div className=\"absolute top-0 left-0 w-1.5 h-full\" style={{ backgroundColor: path.accent }} />\n                              <div className=\"pl-1.5 space-y-1\">\n                                <div className=\"flex justify-between items-center text-[7.5px] font-mono uppercase font-bold\">\n                                  <span style={{ color: path.accent }}>{path.badge}</span>\n                                  <span className=\"text-white/40\">{path.weeks}</span>\n                                </div>\n                                <h3 className=\"text-xs font-extrabold text-white mt-1\">{path.label}</h3>\n                                <p className=\"text-[9.5px] text-white/45 leading-relaxed font-light\">{path.desc}</p>\n                              </div>\n                              <div className=\"pl-1.5 pt-2 mt-2 border-t border-white/5 text-[8.5px] font-mono text-white/30\">\n                                <div><span className=\"text-white/40\">SQUAD:</span> {path.squad}</div>\n                              </div>\n                            </button>\n                          );\n                        })}\n                      </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div className=\"space-y-1.5\">\n                      <label className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50 uppercase tracking-wide block\">Capital Allocation Target (Optional)</label>\n                      <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-2.5\">\n                        {BUDGET_RANGES.map((b) => (\n                          <button\n                            key={b.id}\n                            type=\"button\"\n                            onClick={() => setInputs({ ...inputs, budgetRange: b.id })}\n                            className={`p-3 rounded-xl border text-left transition ${inputs.budgetRange === b.id ? \"border-[#009DFF] bg-[#009DFF]/5\" : \"border-white/5 bg-black/40 hover:border-white/10\"}`}\n                          >\n                            <h4 className=\"text-xs font-bold text-white leading-tight\">{b.label}</h4>\n                            <p className=\"text-[9px] text-white/35 leading-tight mt-1 font-light\">{b.desc}</p>\n                          </button>\n                        ))}\n                      </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div className=\"space-y-1.5\">\n                      <label className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50 uppercase tracking-wide block\">Sponsor Stakeholders (Optional)</label>\n                      <input\n                        type=\"text\"\n                        value={inputs.stakeholders}\n                        onChange={(e) => setInputs({ ...inputs, stakeholders: e.target.value })}\n                        placeholder=\"e.g. VP of Security, Lead Compliance Architect\"\n                        className=\"w-full bg-black/40 border border-white/10 rounded-lg px-4 h-11 text-xs text-white placeholder-white/25 focus:outline-none focus:border-[#009DFF] transition\"\n                      />\n                    </div>\n                  </div>\n                )}\n\n                {/* BOTTOM STEPS BUTTONS */}\n                <div className=\"border-t border-white/5 pt-5 mt-6 flex justify-between items-center\">\n                  <button\n                    type=\"button\"\n                    onClick={() => setActiveStepGate((prev) => (prev - 1) as 1 | 2 | 3)}\n                    disabled={activeStepGate === 1}\n                    className={`px-4 h-9 rounded-lg border text-xs font-mono uppercase transition ${activeStepGate === 1 ? \"border-white/5 text-white/10 cursor-not-allowed\" : \"border-white/10 text-white hover:bg-white/5\"}`}\n                  >\n                    Back\n                  </button>\n                  <div className=\"flex gap-2.5\">\n                    <button\n                      type=\"button\"\n                      onClick={handleSaveDraft}\n                      className=\"px-3.5 h-9 rounded-lg border border-white/10 text-xs font-mono text-white hover:bg-white/5 transition uppercase\"\n                    >\n                      {saved ? \"✓ Saved\" : \"[ Save Draft ]\"}\n                    </button>\n                    {activeStepGate < 3 ? (\n                      <button\n                        type=\"button\"\n                        onClick={handleNextGate}\n                        className=\"px-4 h-9 rounded-lg text-xs font-bold uppercase bg-[#009DFF] text-black hover:bg-[#009DFF]/90 font-mono\"\n                      >\n                        Next Gate\n                      </button>\n                    ) : (\n                      <button\n                        type=\"button\"\n                        onClick={handleCompile}\n                        className=\"px-4 h-9 rounded-lg text-xs font-bold uppercase bg-[#00FF9D] text-black hover:bg-[#00FF9D]/90 font-mono\"\n                      >\n                        Compile SOW Blueprint\n                      </button>\n                    )}\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n              </div>"}}}
